    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>1 cup sweet rice (malt barley)</li>
            <li>6 cups water</li>
            <li>1 cup sugar</li>
            <li>1/4 cup pine nuts or jujubes (optional, for garnish)</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Sikye</li>
            <li>Korean</li>
            <li>Drink</li>
            <li>Sweet</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Rinse the sweet rice in cold water until the water becomes clear.</li>
            <li>In a large pot, combine the sweet rice and water. Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat to low and simmer for about 20-30 minutes until the rice is fully cooked.</li>
            <li>Strain the liquid from the rice using a fine mesh sieve, collecting the liquid in a separate bowl or pot.</li>
            <li>While the liquid is still warm, dissolve sugar in it, stirring until fully combined.</li>
            <li>Allow the sweet rice drink (Sikye) to cool to room temperature and then refrigerate until chilled.</li>
            <li>Serve in glasses, garnished with pine nuts or jujubes if desired.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your refreshing Sikye!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

